 | Disclaimer II is the second album released by the band Seether. This disc  |
 | is a recompilation of the band's first album, Disclaimer, from 2002.       |
 | Although the 12 tracks from the original album are present, they have been |
 | slightly  remixed and do differ from the original. In Europe, the album    |
 | includes four tracks more than its predecessor; in the United States, the  |
 | album has eight extra tracks. In both releases, the featured track is a    |
 | remix of the song "Broken". Amy Lee, the lead singer from Evanescence,     |
 | join Seether vocalist Shaun Morgan in a duet performance on this track.    |
 | It iseth band's most successful album commercially. The album is certified |
 | Platinum Worldwide, going Gold in the US and Canada.                       |
